<express_ref linkend="property_assignment:arm:Property_assignment_arm.Property_representation"/>
and a factor that helps weigh the criticality of the 
<express_ref linkend="risk_definition:arm:Risk_definition_arm.Risk_level"/>.
<note>A negative number for the criticality factor means risk attractive and gives a concave function if increasing, 
a convex if decreasing.  For a risk averse utility function the criticality factor 
should be positive if the function is increasing, negative if decreasing utility.  
The converse applies for risk attractive utility functions.
</note>
</ext_description>
