A <b>Risk_consequence</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> and specifies the outcome of an event.
<note number="1">There may be one or more consequences of an event.</note>
<note number="2">Consequences can range from positive to negative.  However, consequences are always negative for safety aspects.</note>
<note number="3">Consequences can be expressed qualitatively or quantitatively.</note>
</ext_description>
